<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Barcelona sporting director Ramon Planes has all but confirmed Arturo Vidal's departure from the club.</p>

<p>The midfielder was left out of Ronald Koeman's squad for the Catalan giants' pre-season friendly against Gimnastic last weekend and has been heavily linked with a move to Inter Milan.</p>

<p>On Tuesday Planes provided an update on Vidal's future and indicated that the deal to take him from Spain to Italy was edging closer.</p>

<p>Barcelona midfielder Arturo Vidal appears to be on the verge of moving to Inter Milan</p>

<p>Barcelona sporting director Ramon Planes has all but confirmed Vidal's departure from club </p>

<p>'Vidal? It's true that progress is being made in the departure of Arturo Vidal,' Planes said at Miralem Pjanic's unveiling. </p>

<p>'I take this opportunity to thank him for these two years.</p>

<p>'Vidal is in negotiations for an exit, but it's not finalised yet.'</p>

<p>Vidal has made 96 appearances for Barcelona, scoring 11 goals and providing 10 assists, after joining from German giants Bayern Munich in 2018.</p>

<p>The 33-year-old has been vocal in his criticism of Barcelona, criticising the club for being too reliant on Lionel Messi and having too many youth products in the first-team. He slammed the club fro having just '13 professional players'. </p>

<p>Inter MIilan's Antonio Conte has been interested in signing Vidal and move is edging closer</p>
